3 Statistical analyses

he unpaired two-samples Wilcoxon test (also known as Wilcoxon rank sum test or Mann-Whitney U test, Mann-Whitney Wilcoxon test) It is a non-parametric alternative to the unpaired two-samples t-test, which can be used to compare two independent groups of samples. It’s used when your data are not normally distributed.

#♥

library(rstatix)
## 
## Attaching package: 'rstatix'
## The following object is masked from 'package:stats':
## 
##     filter

3.1 Total participants

stat.test1 <- df1 %>%
  rstatix::group_by(glycan) %>%
  rstatix::wilcox_test(value ~ FFA15) %>%
  rstatix::adjust_pvalue(method = "BH") %>%
  rstatix::add_significance() %>%
  rstatix::add_y_position() %>%
  rstatix::add_x_position(x = "glycan")

p1 <- ggplot(df1, aes(x=glycan, y=value, fill=FFA15))
p1 <- p1 + geom_violin(position=position_dodge(),draw_quantiles=c(0.5)) + geom_boxplot(width=0.4, outlier.size = 0.6, position = position_dodge(width =0.9))

p1 <- p1 + stat_compare_means(aes(group=FFA15), label = "p.signif", method="wilcox.test", label.x.npc = 0.5, hide.ns = TRUE, label.y.npc = 0.88, size = 3.8) + facet_wrap(~ glycan, scales="free")
